title: school football | Top performers
text:
Rushing • Brenden Knox, Franklin Heights 
Rushed for 264 yards and three touchdowns on 30 carries in a 56-55 loss to Delaware.
>> Videos | Football highlights from around central Ohio 
>> High-school football results, box scores from Week 9 
• Earl Redman, Whitehall 
Rushed for 250 yards and two touchdowns on 18 carries in a 35-12 win over Madison Plains.
• Cullen Moore, Delaware 
Rushed for 231 yards and five touchdowns on 25 carries in the win over Franklin Heights.
• Sean Sullivan, Jonathan Alder 
Rushed for 218 yards and two touchdowns on 37 carries in a 28-22 win over River Valley.
Passing • Ridge Durbin, Danville 
Passed for 341 yards and four touchdowns and added 141 rushing yards and a score in a 41-0 win over Lucas.
• Will Phillis, Hilliard Bradley 
Passed for 277 yards and four touchdowns in a 34-31 win over Dublin Scioto.
• Patrick Robinson, Hamilton Township 
Passed for 272 yards and a touchdown in a 55-34 win over Logan Elm.
• Michael Camp, Circleville 
Passed for 260 yards and four touchdowns and added 139 rushing yards and a score in a 38-7 win over Amanda-Clearcreek.
Receiving • Tyrece Speaight, Upper Arlington 
Had five receptions for 157 yards and three touchdowns in a 39-20 win over Westland.
• Simon Romine, Heath 
Had three receptions for 129 yards and two touchdowns in a 53-27 win over Lakewood.
